  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Methodologies for Enhancing Model InterpretabilitySeveral methodologies have been proposed and evaluated with the aim of enhancing the interpretability of machine learning models, including LLMs.",
    "A prevalent theme in these studies is the use of post-hoc interpretability techniques, which analyze model outputs to deduce the factors influencing decisions [28,36,37].",
    "Techniques such as feature importance analysis and decision tree approximations were shown to provide valuable insights into model reasoning, albeit with limitations in capturing the full complexity of LLMs [38,26,39,40].",
    "Another approach that garnered attention involves the integration of interpretability directly into the model architecture, through methods like attention mechanisms and transparent layers designed to offer more direct insight into the decision-making process [38,41,34,36,32].",
    "Despite these advancements, challenges remain in achieving a satisfactory level of interpretability without compromising model performance, underscoring the ongoing need for innovative solutions."
  ],
